Package: vldaft
Title: Non-Proportional Hazards Accelerated Failure Time Regression
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Keaven", "Anderson", , "keaven_anderson@merck.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
    )
Description: Fits the Anderson (1991) accelerated failure time regression
    model where both location and scale are functions of covariates, and
    scale can depend on location via a polynomial in the linear predictor.
    Supports Weibull, logistic, normal, Cauchy, and gamma error
    distributions with right censoring, left censoring, and left
    truncation. Provides a stand-alone fitting function and gamlss2
    family extensions. Estimation is Newton-Raphson with a modified
    Cholesky decomposition, implemented in both C and Rust.
License: GPL (>= 3)
URL: https://keaven.github.io/vldaft/, https://github.com/keaven/vldaft
BugReports: https://github.com/keaven/vldaft/issues
NeedsCompilation: yes
SystemRequirements: Cargo (>= 1.70.0) and rustc, the Rust compiler
    (install from https://rustup.rs). Confidential example data
    live in the companion repository https://github.com/keaven/vldaft.data.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports: survival, stats
Suggests: gamlss2, knitr, litedown, rmarkdown, testthat (>= 3.0.0)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Additional_repositories: https://gamlss-dev.r-universe.dev
Config/testthat/edition: 3
